###
### 📱 SMS NOTIFICATIONS API TESTS
### Base endpoint: /api/sms-notif
###
### This file contains tests for SMS notification endpoints using Twilio.
### Update the variables below and run requests with :Rest run
###
### Authentication required:
### - x-api-key: Global API key
###
### Note: Phone numbers must be in E.164 format (+[country code][number])
### Example: +14155552671 (US), +442071838750 (UK), +8613800138000 (China)
###

### ============================================
### VARIABLES - UPDATE THESE FOR YOUR ENVIRONMENT
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiKey = your-api-key-here
@phoneNumber = +1234567890
@phone2 = +19876543210
@phone3 = +15555555555
@phone4 = +14155552671
@smsBody = Hello from HyggeHub! Thank you for subscribing to our updates.
@smsSender = HyggeHub
@shortMessage = Thanks!
@longMessage = This is a longer message to test SMS handling with more content. It includes multiple sentences and should still be delivered successfully via Twilio's SMS service. This tests the character limit handling.
@invalidPhone = 1234567890
@invalidPhone2 = not-a-phone
@emptyMessage = 


### ============================================
### POST - Send SMS Notification
### ============================================

### send-sms-single-recipient-with-sender
# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS to single recipient with custom sender name
# Handler: backend/app/api/sms-notif/handler/send-sms.ts:7
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": "{{smsSender}}"
}


### send-sms-single-recipient-without-sender
# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS without custom sender name (uses Twilio default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-multiple-recipients
# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS to multiple recipients (array format)
# Returns success/failure status for each recipient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": [
    "{{phoneNumber}}",
    "{{phone2}}",
    "{{phone3}}"
  ],
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-multiple-recipients-with-sender
# Expected: 200 OK
# Sends SMS to multiple recipients with custom sender
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": [
    "{{phoneNumber}}",
    "{{phone2}}",
    "{{phone3}}",
    "{{phone4}}"
  ],
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": "{{smsSender}}"
}


### send-sms-short-message
# Expected: 200 OK
# Tests: Very short message content
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{shortMessage}}"
}


### send-sms-long-message
# Expected: 200 OK (or may be split into multiple SMS)
# Tests: Long message content (may exceed single SMS limit)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{longMessage}}"
}


### send-sms-invalid-phone-format
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Phone number not in E.164 format
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{invalidPhone}}",
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-invalid-phone-string
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Invalid phone number (non-numeric)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{invalidPhone2}}",
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-missing-body
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Missing required body field
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}


### send-sms-empty-body
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Empty message body
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{emptyMessage}}"
}


### send-sms-missing-recipient
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Missing required to field
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-empty-recipients-array
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Empty array for recipients
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": [],
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-mixed-valid-invalid-recipients
# Expected: 200 OK (partial success)
# Tests: Some valid recipients, some invalid
# Should return success for valid, failure for invalid
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": [
    "{{phoneNumber}}",
    "{{invalidPhone}}",
    "{{phone2}}"
  ],
  "body": "{{smsBody}}"
}


### send-sms-empty-request
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# Tests: Completely empty request body
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### send-sms-null-sender
# Expected: 200 OK
# Tests: Explicitly null sender name (should use default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": null
}


### send-sms-empty-sender
# Expected: 200 OK
# Tests: Empty string sender name (should use default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sms-notif
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "body": "{{smsBody}}",
  "senderName": ""
}
